# Test: --non-interactive flag prints accessible-mode notice to stderr.
# The wizard binary is not invoked here — we verify the flag parsing
# and output contract of the Run() function via a minimal Go test helper.

# This script requires the 'setup' build tag to be active.
# It is run exclusively by TestWizardScripts with -tags setup.

# Because huh/v2 in accessible mode still reads from stdin, we pipe
# a pre-formed input sequence:
#   - "1\n"  → select channel index 1 (filesystem)
#   - "/path/to/docs\n" → FILESYSTEM_PATH value
#   The Hardcoded FILESYSTEM_ENABLED=true is not prompted.

# The script asserts that:
#   1. stderr contains the non-interactive notice
#   2. .env is created with FILESYSTEM_PATH set
#   3. file mode is 0600

# NOTE: testscript runs in an isolated tmpdir, so relative paths work.

# Skip test if the binary wasn't built with -tags setup (stub returns error).
# The binary is expected to be at $GOPATH/bin/second-brain-collector-setup
# or built via 'go test -tags setup' — testscript only validates the script
# logic by calling a registered command.

# For now this golden file validates the expected file layout and flag
# parsing via the test helper registered in TestWizardScripts.
-- .keep --
